Experience Web and Communications Specialist Stanford University June 2014  – Present (1 year 3 months) Under minimal supervision, the Web and Communications Specialist develops and oversees web and communications channels. Job duties include: 

• Leading the design, development and maintenance of several project-specific websites, including written and multimedia content, quality control, usability, etc.; 

• Developing, distributing and maintaining digital communications; 

• Serving as a resource to staff on website and communications design and maintenance, social media, communications and technology; 

• Providing technical expertise to SBC on front and back end web development; 

• Bringing innovative multimedia and technology strategies to meet organizational goals and enhance SBC's reach and impact; 

• Leading web strategy and maintenance; 

• Troubleshooting problems and interacting with users (staff, project leaders, community) to improve user experience; 

• Maintaining, analyzing, and communicating web data; 

• Evaluating third-party technologies for functionality, accessibility, security, and maintainability; 

• Supporting end users, maintaining applications and content management tools; 

• Growing a digital community on behalf of, and while representing, Stanford Blood Center. CTO Block122 August 2012  – Present (3 years 1 month) San Francisco Bay Area As Chief Technology Officer and Vice-President of Block122, Inc., I am directly responsible for overseeing the primary design and back-end development, as well as executing the front-end development, of the corporate website and online presence. In the broadest sense, my role is comprised of envisioning the company’s service offerings as a web-based business, overseeing and sometimes directly designing/developing its branding assets, leading the implementation of web, mobile and desktop applications, and planning for risk and growth. 

Additionally, in conference with the other corporate officers, I am responsible for finally creating and managing the brand direction of all print and web media/advertising; I also perform managerial duties in the branding and technology department, including hiring and managing design/development/web operations staff (collaborating with the COO, CFO and HR), sourcing vendors for printing and web development contract services, and providing accurate budget reports and projections for the branding/technology departments. 

Finally, I work with the other officers to maintain consistency of branding and company culture across all social media outlets. Owner / Designer Industrious Monkey January 2006  – Present (9 years 8 months) As sole-proprietor of a web design and development business, I have had a hand in every phase of the production process, from consultation and contracting, to design, to implementation and maintenance. I have worked with small businesses to develop their branding from the ground up, including logo and collateral design, web presence, and email marketing design and strategy.  

As an independent contractor, I have designed and built sites with a social media focus for small and mid-sized businesses, a Fortune 200 company, charitable organizations and several tech start-ups. 

